Most people (50-80% with coronavirus infection have no symptoms. The next major group is mild symptoms.
Both these groups have lower mortality with coronavirus than influenza virus. So that is great news.
Unfortunately, asymptomatic people are most likely to create new patients.
And those at high risk (over 79, heart, lung, immune disease,etc), are those who are medically mandated to get the annual flu shot, well, they die about 20% if the time. That means they survive 80% of the time.
